222.bio_narrative: Bellatrix Lestrange is a 49-year-old female with a history of chronic kidney disease. Known for her spirited personality, she has faced many challenges in her life, but her recent health concerns have been at the forefront. Bellatrix has exhibited signs of significant renal dysfunction, including persistent fatigue and swelling in her extremities. Socially, she remains actively engaged with her family, though her health conditions have impacted her daily activities. Over recent months, she has been closely monitored by healthcare professionals, leading to the decision for management through dialysis, further necessitating a tunneled central venous catheter insertion.

210.bio_narrative: Kendall Roy is a 37-year-old male with a complex personality and a history of anxiety and stress-related conditions. He has experienced chest pain intermittently over the past few months, prompting this current assessment. Kendall lives independently and is notably influenced by his family's legacy as well as professional dynamics with his brother. He denies any previous history of heart disease but acknowledges a high-stress lifestyle and inconsistent exercise routines. His social determinants include private health insurance and an active lifestyle in urban New York.

232.bio_narrative: Leslie Knope is a dedicated public servant known for her unyielding passion for community development in Pawnee, Indiana. Over the past five years, she has experienced increasing discomfort in her jaw, affecting her daily life and responsibilities. Initially, Leslie tried conservative measures, including various orthodontic suggestions, but found no relief. Her symptoms worsened, prompting her to seek further evaluation.  Recently, she has been diagnosed with a significant overbite requiring surgical correction through a Bilateral Sagittal Split Osteotomy (BSSO). The surgical intervention is aimed at restoring both her dental occlusion and facial balance. In addition, Leslie is committed to improving her personal health and is engaging in physical activity to manage stress effectively.

234.bio_narrative: Max Black is a 35-year-old female who has been experiencing ongoing dental issues resulting from prior surgeries. Despite the challenges, she maintains a positive outlook on her health and well-being. Max has a strong support system, particularly from her emergency contact, her sister, Mona. Having grown up in Brooklyn, she cherishes her close-knit community and often participates in local gatherings. Recently, she noted discomfort due to bone loss in her maxillary region, leading to difficulties in her dietary habits. The decision for a bone graft was reached following imaging that revealed bone resorption, which she hopes will improve her quality of life significantly.

211.bio_narrative:
Dr. Gregory House is a brilliant but unconventional diagnostician who works at Princeton-Plainsboro Teaching Hospital. Known for his acerbic wit and sharp intellect, Dr. House often clashes with hospital policies and authority figures. Despite his unconventional methods, he is deeply committed to solving medical mysteries, driven by a personal history of chronic pain from a leg injury, which also influences his relationship with patients and staff.

In recent weeks, Dr. House has faced a renewed sense of fatigue and intermittent chest discomfort, prompting him to pursue further evaluation. Although he has no significant prior medical history, his clinical judgment and persistent nature led him to seek a thorough assessment of his cardiovascular health. The recent ECG and stress testing revealed normal results that suggest he is at low risk for significant heart issues, allowing him to focus on his work and continue making groundbreaking contributions to medicine.

Despite being in good physical shape due to his regular training for triathlons, he has experienced some episodes of chest discomfort lately. Howard is motivated to address potential health issues as he aspires to be healthy for himself and for his family.

Sophie is single and enjoys spending time with her friends, particularly Max Black, who has been a source of support during this time of uncertainty. She is hopeful that the results will provide clarity and allow her to continue with her active lifestyle.

Carla has no significant past medical history and except for her recent symptoms, she leads a fairly active lifestyle. She enjoys hiking and weekend outings with friends. 217.bio_narrative: Dr. Allison Cameron is a 40-year-old physician specializing in immunology. She leads a busy professional life, which often leaves her little time for exercise. Recently, she has noticed a change in her physical capabilities, particularly experiencing shortness of breath during her work with patients. Having no previous history of cardiovascular problems, she was initially hesitant to seek medical help. However, encouraged by her colleagues, she underwent a thorough examination which revealed 80% stenosis in the left anterior descending artery. Although she experiences symptoms, there were no other major issues detected. She is irreversibly dedicated to helping others but recognizes she needs to take her health seriously. Outside of work, Allison is single and active in various community health initiatives. As she continues her healing journey, she’s prioritized lifestyle changes to better accommodate her health.

218.bio_narrative: Miranda Bailey is a 41-year-old female physician with a history of significant responsibility as a chief resident. In recent weeks, she noticed an unusual heart murmur during her routine check-up, which prompted further investigation with an ECG showing nonspecific abnormalities. With no significant past medical history, she has been active and maintaining a healthy lifestyle, although her recent symptoms have caused her enough concern to seek medical advice. Family support, particularly from her husband, Leonard, has been crucial as they navigate health measures together. As she continues monitoring her cardiac health, Penny remains optimistic about receiving the necessary care to address her symptoms.

220.bio_narrative:
George Costanza is a 54-year-old male diagnosed with end-stage renal disease (ESRD) that has led to significant challenges in his daily life. Previously, he was a vibrant member of his community, working in a local job that provided him with a sense of purpose. However, with the onset of his health issues, George has struggled to maintain his responsibilities and lifestyle.  

His social life has been affected, stemming from both physical limitations and the emotional toll of his condition. Friends like Jerry and Elaine have offered support, but George recognizes the need for professional management of his health, particularly concerning his renal status. He has dealt with hypertension for years but has not had previous complications until recently. 

George's family history reveals chronic kidney disease, particularly in his father, which raises concerns regarding his future. His wish is to regain some normalcy in his life by managing his condition with a detailed treatment plan. He has expressed a desire for stability through dialysis therapy and is actively seeking appropriate supervision and support.

221.bio_narrative:
Lisa Cuddy first presented to the clinic with complaints of palpitations and episodes of dizziness over the past few weeks. These episodes have been occurring more frequently, particularly during times of stress. Patient denies any previous cardiac history and reports no family history of heart disease. 

Professionally, Lisa is a hospital administrator and often experiences high levels of stress due to her demanding job. In her social history, she enjoys running and yoga to manage stress but has noticed a decrease in her stamina recently. She lives in Princeton, NJ, and is independent in her living arrangements. 

On her last visit, she reported feeling anxious about her symptoms, prompting her to seek a cardiology consult. With the reassurance from previous clinical evaluations, she is hopeful about finding answers and resolving her symptoms.

223.bio_narrative:
Caroline Channing is a 34-year-old female with a diagnosis of chronic kidney disease secondary to polycystic kidney disease. Initially diagnosed at age 28, she has been on dialysis for the past two years. Caroline works as a marketing executive in New York City and has faced challenges managing her personal and professional life due to her health condition. She has recently moved to Brooklyn to be closer to her family and to access better medical facilities.

Socially, Caroline enjoys spending time with her friends and has a supportive network that includes her college roommates. She maintains a healthy lifestyle by engaging in yoga and meditation. Despite her health challenges, she remains optimistic and focused on her career. Caroline has expressed a strong desire for a permanent dialysis access solution to improve her quality of life. 

Family history is significant for chronic diseases; her mother suffered from type 2 diabetes and her father passed away from heart disease. Caroline does not smoke and drinks alcohol occasionally. She is proactive in managing her health and regularly attends all her scheduled appointments.

224.bio_narrative: April Ludgate is a 35-year-old woman originally from Pawnee, IN, who has been living with end-stage renal disease. She has been on dialysis for the last four years, struggling with diet restrictions and the emotional toll of her chronic condition. Her sense of humor helps her cope with being single and living a somewhat unusual lifestyle. April is independent but has a close friendship with Andy Dwyer, who serves as her emergency contact and confidant. She has no prior surgical history and has thoroughly researched the kidney transplant process to prepare herself for the changes ahead. Her main concerns include the potential for a successful operation and recovery. April has expressed willingness to explore living donation options among her friends and family.

225.bio_narrative:

Margaery has been suffering from chronic renal failure for the past two years, attributed to undiagnosed glomerulonephritis. She enjoys a vibrant social life but has felt increasingly fatigued due to her health condition. 

Margaery's family history is largely free of kidney diseases, but there have been instances of autoimmune disorders. Socially, she maintains a close relationship with her grandmother, Olenna Tyrell, who serves as her emergency contact. She is aware of the need for a transplant and is actively engaged in discussions with her healthcare team regarding the procedure. Margaery is motivated to regain her health and return to her active lifestyle, participating in noble pursuits and caring for her family.

nan.bio_narrative: Ron Swanson, a 50-year-old male, has a history of recurrent chest pain that has begun to affect his quality of life. He is divorced and shares custody of his two children with his ex-wife. Despite his gruff exterior, he values his family deeply and is committed to improving his health for their sake. Ron’s father had a history of heart disease, which adds further impetus for him to take these warnings seriously. He has been strongly advised to adjust his diet and engage more actively in physical activities.
